00:55:52.500 --> 00:55:54.920
is giving people
availability bias.

00:55:54.920 --> 00:55:58.000
Because true, active
opportunities--

00:55:58.000 --> 00:56:00.260
they're basically
long-duration arbitrages

00:56:00.260 --> 00:56:02.600
that have a lot of
noise in the short run.

00:56:02.600 --> 00:56:05.760
And if you match
short-duration capital

00:56:05.760 --> 00:56:07.990
with a long-duration
opportunity,

00:56:07.990 --> 00:56:10.000
they end up contributing
to the anomaly.

00:56:10.000 --> 00:56:11.960
And the more information
is available,

00:56:11.960 --> 00:56:14.610
the more people can buy
and sell at their whims

00:56:14.610 --> 00:56:17.450
and their emotions,
in my thoughts,

00:56:17.450 --> 00:56:19.320
it's actually making
these things worse.

00:56:19.320 --> 00:56:23.850
Like the more you have
availability and access to edge

00:56:23.850 --> 00:56:26.360
that will give you
overconfidence in whatever idea

00:56:26.360 --> 00:56:28.010
or story you're
believing in, I think

00:56:28.010 --> 00:56:31.150
it's going to make these
things even better, frankly.

