backtest willy-nilly,

00:56:40.050 --> 00:56:43.740
without understanding
robustness, frameworks,

00:56:43.740 --> 00:56:46.270
like competitive dynamics
of market places,

00:56:46.270 --> 00:56:48.150
they're going to just
backtest-- oh wow,

00:56:48.150 --> 00:56:50.360
this is like easy
money, start doing

00:56:50.360 --> 00:56:55.360
that-- it's just contributing
more and more to the problems.

00:56:55.360 --> 00:56:59.760
So I think they're actually
more sustainable now.

00:56:59.760 --> 00:57:04.450
I think information just forces
people to make worse decisions.

00:57:04.450 --> 00:57:05.930
Because it's more available.

00:57:05.930 --> 00:57:09.290
It's more in their face
they've got more saliency

00:57:09.290 --> 00:57:12.570
and they just make
worse decisions.

