you're going to be the
worst active investor ever.

01:03:14.520 --> 01:03:18.880
So the vast majority of
people should just not

01:03:18.880 --> 01:03:22.830
pay all these extra fees for all
these crazy marketed products.

01:03:22.830 --> 01:03:23.890
It's all crap.

01:03:23.890 --> 01:03:27.826
You can buy it way cheaper, more
effectively at Vanguard, right?

01:03:27.826 --> 01:03:29.450
And you don't have
a psychology problem

01:03:29.450 --> 01:03:31.324
because the market's
down 30, you're down 30,

01:03:31.324 --> 01:03:34.350
you're just like, well whatever,
I'm relatively good to go.

01:03:34.350 --> 01:03:37.630
The minute go on
active angle, you

01:03:37.630 --> 01:03:41.830
take on a whole new level
of psychology problems.

01:03:41.830 --> 01:03:43.179
And that's why it works.

01:03:43.179 --> 01:03:44.970
Because now you're in
this competitive game

01:03:44.970 --> 01:03:48.650
where you've got to be that
weird, wired person that

01:03:48.650 --> 01:03:50.330
does crazy stuff.

01:03:50.330 --> 01:03:53.910
And be willing to be the
bag holder at maximum pain.

01:03:53.910 --> 01:03:56.490
Because then you'll capture
all the rents of this active

01:03:56.490 --> 01:03:59.780
strategy where all the people
that don't have that discipline

01:03:59.780 --> 01:04:00.600
can't.

01:04:00.600 --> 01:04:02.740
It's all about that
relativeness which seems

01:04:02.740 --> 01:04:04.510
to drive this risk premium.

01:04:04.510 --> 01:04:08.610
So Warren Buffett says this
because he understands this.

01:04:08.610 --> 01:04:10.900
And he knows that
unless you're wired

01:04:10.900 --> 01:04:14.530
to deal with years of just
looking like an idiot,

01:04:14.530 --> 01:04:17.730
you're way better off
being a passive person.

01:04:17.730 --> 01:04:19.500
Because otherwise
you are going to sell

01:04:19.500 --> 01:04:21.450
at the worst possible time.

01:04:21.450 --> 01:04:23.710
So that's why he makes
that recommendation.

01:04:23.710 --> 01:04:25.760
That's why I make
that recommendation.

01:04:25.760 --> 01:04:27.150
This is not for everyone.

01:04:27.150 --> 01:04:28.250
It's the worst.

01:04:28.250 --> 01:04:32.470
It gives you like balding
gray hair like I got, right?

01:04:32.470 --> 01:04:34.760
If you want to be
chilling out on the beach

01:04:34.760 --> 01:04:37.890
and not worry about life, just
go buy your Vanguard funds

01:04:37.890 --> 01:04:40.240
and chill out and you
keep your hair nice.

01:04:40.240 --> 01:04:42.580
It'll stay brown and you
don't have to worry about it.

01:04:42.580 --> 01:04:45.430
Active investing is going
to make you go insane.

01:04:45.430 --> 01:04:47.430
And that's probably why
you get a risk premium--

01:04:47.430 --> 01:04:48.710
because it sucks.

01:04:48.710 --> 01:04:51.370
You know it's terrible.

01:04:51.370 --> 01:04:52.430
But that's life.

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:54.672
Markets are not
efficient in the sense

01:04:54.672 --> 01:04:56.820
that prices always
reflect fundamentals.

01:04:56.820 --> 01:04:58.830
But they're insanely
competitive.

01:04:58.830 --> 01:05:00.690
So it's not like
money grows on trees.

01:05:00.690 --> 01:05:03.544
There's always a
premium and a cost.

01:05:03.544 --> 01:05:04.960
And it's just a
matter of like, am

01:05:04.960 --> 01:05:07.860
I suited to take this cost
better than the person offering

01:05:07.860 --> 01:05:09.510
that risk premium to me.

01:05:09.510 --> 01:05:13.310
And value people earn that
because they're usually weird.

01:05:13.310 --> 01:05:16.990
They can feel like an idiot at
the cocktail party and be like,

01:05:16.990 --> 01:05:18.270
I don't care.

01:05:18.270 --> 01:05:22.220
A lot of people
can't do that, so.

01:05:22.220 --> 01:05:23.340
We'll go over here.

01:05:23.340 --> 01:05:24.286
Sir?

01:05:24.286 --> 01:05:25.910
AUDIENCE: So I have
a couple questions.

01:05:25.910 --> 01:05:27.210
Number one is are
